<plot>To what extent can familial memoirs be (re-)experienced and to what end? 'Point of Departure' converges scattered pieces of family history as Iris Ng combines audio interviews, archival footage, and sites on 16mm of Hong Kong to test the parallels between architectural spaces and the strength of personal memories.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?437149</url></doc>
